name: Beautifully renovated family apartment
description:
Our apartment was completely renovated in 2021. The atmosphere of the house from 1912 has been preserved by retaining original details such as the ensuite and the fireplace.
Special is the unobstructed view, the many books and the size of the apartment!
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is about 100 metres from the famous Vondelpark; you see the park from the front windows. One street away there is a tram but you can also walk or bike in 10 minutes (through the Vondelpark) to Leidseplein, Van Gogh museum, Rijksmuseum, etc. The direct environment is calm but around the corner it’s full of nice shops, boutiques and good restaurants. Downstairs is a grocery and across the street a cosy Italian restaurant, in summertime with a nice terrace at our square. Around the corner there is a butcher, grocery and supermarket. Just crossing the street there is a large and attractive playground for kids.
host_about:
We are a family of 4 people. Annemiek is a journalist and writes children's literature.  Fenice (22 years old) and Mare (18) are our daughters. I'm an architect and urban designer at Studio Vinke, my own company.
Since 1997 we live in Amsterdam.

Information about our work: Linkedin, Annemiek Neefjes or Stefan Bödecker

name: Historical sailing ship Monnickendam and Amsterdam
description: Welcome on board of our historical sailing ship "Chateauroux", in the summer sailing the Dutch waters and docked in the historical harbour town Monnickendam (20 min from Amsterdam) or in Amsterdam. Experience the unique and free way of living on the water, like many local Monnickendammers and Amsterdammers do. Our skipper will be happy to tell you all about the ship, sailing and the city.
neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam (Pontsteiger) - From the northern Pontsteiger, you are in the city in no time. The nearby Westerpark blends green spaces, a lively creative and nightlife scene, and iconic architecture. Along with its regular exhibitions, markets and festivals, the converted Westergasfabriek gasworks contains indie shops, eclectic eateries, an art-house cinema, a brewery and a dance club. Nearby, the Museum Het Schip is the focus of a residential area of red-brick Amsterdam School buildings.
host_about: I live in Amsterdam, either on our family owned sailing ship Chateauroux or on my private sailing ship. In the summers I'm often out sailing on the Dutch waters (or beyond!). I also own a coworking space and coffee bar called BounceSpace in the city centre of Amsterdam. You're welcome to come by there for coffee or for a work spot. I"ll be happy to tell you more about living on a ship in Amsterdam and of course where to go during your stay :)

name: ★ STYLISH FAMILY HOME - CITY CENTER
description: Welcome to our lovely home! You've come to the right place to experience Amsterdam as it is - a stylish family home in a lovely neighboorhood in Amsterdam City Center.
neighborhood_overview:
THE NEIGHBORHOOD:

We are in the city centre in a quiet neighbourhood (Helmersbuurt). The neighbourhood is very popular and known for its nice bars, restaurants and plenty of facilities for families with children. Recently new (coffee) bars have been opened around the corner and across the street is one of the best bakeries in Amsterdam; 't Vlaams Broodhuys.

We are in walking distance from the Vondelpark (famous its quiet places, great terraces and free concerts) with and many other attractions such as the museum square, Leidse Square, Jordaan, the famous 'negen straatjes' and pop venue Paradiso. The high class PC Hooftstraat shopping street is also in walking distance.

Paid parking space is widely available in our street. There are several supermarkets (discount, organic and 'normal') in our area, all within a three minutes walk. You can take a 10 min bike ride (or just one of the trams close to our home) to the Albert Cuip Market or the Dam Square an
host_about:
I am a mom of three and a web designer. We love living in the city in our  spacious and cosy home in the middle of the city. I can't live without my family, friends, music, my IPhone and my home town Amsterdam. 

My style of travelling is 'live like the locals do' - try to get off the beaten track by just walking around town or asking advice to local people in a bar or grocery store. I love to make myself at home and offer the possibilities for other people to do the same when they visit me. Oh, and I am crazy about lighthouses...

name: Familyfriendly Suite incl breakfast
description: Our charming suite with sitting/sleeping area comfortably fits 2-4 pers. Located in our farmhouse @ 10 mins drive from city centre. Enjoy the countryside and the city centre. Breakfast included (in nice weather in the garden). Excellent free wifi. Towels  (fresh daily) and sheets/blankets included. Coffeemaker, water boiler, fridge present in suite. Nice garden by the water to relax, with trampoline and small football field.
neighborhood_overview:
Ransdorp is one of the most authentic places in the very close vicinity of Amsterdam centre (10 minutes). The house is located in Ransdorp, a typical Dutch village with characteristic wooden houses set around a monumental tower; where circa 1645 Rembrandt made many drawings. The town is called the 'Garden of Amsterdam'.
Our well located country suite makes it easy for you to visit the busy city centre of Amsterdam with its many museums, the Anne Frank House, shops, bars, restaurants and canals.
You can also enjoy the tranquility of Waterland: taking our bicycles (free) or boat (rent) that will take you through country site roads, lakes, outstretched meadows, polder landscape, and picturesque villages with wooden houses and farms. You can just relax in our garden and enjoy the amazingly panoramic view. The village of Ransdorp is 20 minutes drive from tourist places Marken, Volendam, Edam and Zaanse Schans.
host_about:
My husband and I have travelled extensively all over the world and have tried to learn through our good experiences as well as from our bad ones. We love traveling, nature, beaches, mountains, cities, good food, great wines, dancing, movies, reading, sports, and last but not least playing with our 2 sons.
We are sure you will enjoy staying in our country house in the close vicinity of Amsterdam Centre as much as we enjoy living here. We like to mix intimacy with good service and the freedom to enjoy, what is for us, a wonderful place to be yourself.

description:
Prived sunny room with a big terrace on the island of Wittenburg in a quiet part of the center of Amsterdam.
Wittenburg Island is a part of the city centre where in 1700 the Dutch ships where built. The Maritime Museum is around the corner and the central station close by. name: Sailing ship LOTUS, unique group accommodation
description:
Welcome aboard the historic sailing ship Lotus!

A comfortable, atmospheric, and affordable group stay in Amsterdam. Sleep on the water with all the comforts of land: cozy beds, a full kitchen, and warm maritime charm.

Located in the vibrant NDSM district, surrounded by creative warehouses, lively cafés, and authentic restaurants. Just a 10-minute free ferry ride to Central Station and the city center.
neighborhood_overview:
The former NDSM Amsterdam ship wharf is a stunning hangout. Just 10 minutes by free ferry from Amsterdam Central Station.
A former shipyard located on the banks of the River IJ in Amsterdam Noord, the NDSM Wharf has blossomed into an enormous cultural hotspot in recent years with a vibrant artist community and an ever-expanding variety of bars and restaurants including a city beach with a stunning view on the Amsterdam skyline. With grounds exceeding the size of ten football pitches, the area hosts multi-disciplinary festivals, performances, exhibitions, dance parties and a wide range of other events in unique, post-industrial surroundings.
host_about:
Hallo, ik ben Olaf!
Ik ben de trotse kapitein van twee charmante antieke zeilschepen die in de zomer rondvaren door het adembenemende UNESCO-werelderfgoed van de Waddenzee en haar eilanden. In de winter ligt mijn schip Lotus voor je klaar in Amsterdam – kom gerust aan boord en geniet van een onvergetelijk verblijf!

name: Stylish apartment close to major museums
description:
Ideal for a couple, my one-bedroom apartment is in the vibrant neighborhood of de Pijp. It's ideally located for culture vultures, foodies, and shopping fans alike.

The Van Gogh Museum and countless brunch restaurants and boutiques are a short walk away - as is the famous Albertcuypmarkt. Nearby metro and tram connections will get you everywhere you need to go, including to/from the airport.

Tourist registration number:
0363 CA01 0CB4 B5A9 C22A
neighborhood_overview:
Now well-established as the hippest area of Amsterdam (and one of the priciest to live) de Pijp has everything that locals could crave. There’s the beautiful Sarphatipark, bustling Albert Cuypstraat market, and enough shops, bars, cafés and restaurants orbiting those to keep locals and visitors entertained for quite some time.

Originally built for Amsterdam’s workers during the 1800s to ease overpopulation in the Jordaan area, the neighbourhood has been re-purposed in the 21st Century by students, affluent singles and trendy young families who’ve settled in the area. With that, dozens of bars, cafés and boutiques have sprung up to service a population looking for good coffee and unique retail experiences.

But it’s the street market which still provides the heart and soul of the area. Held six days per week for over a century, it’s here, in the concentrated stream of grocery shoppers, that you’ll see a real slice of life with more locals (read ex-pats as well as Am
host_about: I'm 44-year-old copywriter from England, living and working in beautiful Amsterdam since December 2013. It's an easy-going city but it's also packed with vibrant neighbourhoods, great nightlife and countless world-class cultural destinations. When I'm not in Amsterdam, I love to go exploring other countries and cities. How about you?

name: Spacious Apartment near Westerpark
description: Located in a quiet residential area next to Westerpark. 5-10 min from the centre by bus or bike. Cozy, yet modern apartment with a large living space, lots of natural light, bedroom with a 160 x 200 cm bed, bathroom with shower, kitchen + balcony facing the gardens.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is called Spaarndammerbuurt. A lovely area that used to be working class but has developed a lot over the past decade. It features some great architecture from the beginning of the 20th century of the famous 'Amsterdamse School'. You can also find shops, bars and restaurants on the mean street at a 5 minute walk. Like pretty much all of Amsterdam, the area is very safe and quiet both during the day and night.

The Spaarndammerbuurt is located just north of the Westerpark and Westergasfabriek, a nice park / cultural area which is very popular with locals and in which you can have a great time during the day and the night.
host_about:

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam Oost / Amstedam East

Amsterdam East is a residential district in Amsterdam, popular under Amsterdam locals. It lies between the Amstel River in the west and the IJ in the east
The Plantage, which lies east and south-east of Waterlooplein, holds many delights, among them the Hortus Botanicus and the zoo Artis. Directly south of the Plantage is the Oosterpark, the first large park financed by the municipality of Amsterdam as it dates from 1891. The Vondelpark is older and larger, but that initially was a private project. Activities can be undertaken in the park, and a visit to the Tropenmuseum shouldn't be missed. The Dapperbuurt is known for the second largest market of Amsterdam after the Albert Cuyp Market. It has been a designated market street since 1910. Products for sale aim to a Dutch Antillean, Moroccan, Surinamese and Turkish clientele, reflecting the ethnic make-up of the area.

neighborhood_overview:
The Oud-Zuid is arguably the elegant heart of Amsterdam, and is one of the city’s most prestigious cultural districts.
Amsterdam’s elegant Oud-Zuid (Old-South) was developed over a century ago as a cultural gateway to the city, at the tip of what was previously a boggy polder. It’s home to Rijksmuseum, Stedelijk Museum, and Van Gogh Museum – all of which exhibit the highlights of Western art. The nearby Vondelpark – created in the style of an English landscape garden – is the city’s most popular playground and is a magnet for picnickers and visitors who flock in their droves during the summer months to the numerous outdoor performances that take place there.
Oud-Zuid is one of the city’s most desirable addresses, the real estate is Amsterdam’s most expensive and the residents are arguably the most privileged. Amsterdammers dub the area ‘het reservaat’ (the reservation), but you can leave your passport at home – just don’t forget your credit card: some of the chicest boutiques

name: Stylish Apartment in a Lively Neighbourhood
description:
Indulge in an authentic Amsterdam experience in our beautiful apartment in the vibrant neighborhood of Amsterdam Oost.

The apartment is located on the street of the Dapper Market and is walking distance from a diverse range of shops, restaurants, and cafes, including the lively Javastraat, Oosterpark, and the famous Brouwerij het IJ.

The apartment has a large terrace that’s perfect for enjoying your morning coffee or evening wine.

neighborhood_overview:
The Dapper neighborhood in Amsterdam is a fantastic destination for tourists who are looking to experience the city's authentic lifestyle. Located in the eastern part of the city, this colorful and vibrant neighborhood offers a wide range of attractions and activities for visitors of all ages and interests.

One of the most popular attractions in the Dapper neighborhood is the famous Dapper Market, which has been held on the streets of the neighborhood since 1910. The market offers an abundance of fresh produce, flowers, clothing, artwork, and much more. It's the perfect place to soak up the local atmosphere, haggle with vendors, and sample delicious food and drinks.

For visitors interested in the history of the Dapper neighborhood, the Tropenmuseum is a must-visit destination. This museum is dedicated to the cultural diversity of the world and boasts an extensive collection of ethnographic art objects, photography, musical instruments, films, and more.

Live where all Amsterdamers want to live. Cheerful bright room in a historic canal house. Close to many museums & Rembrandsplein & yet wonderfully quiet. Private room: 1 bed or 2 beds (depending on booking), shower & toilet ensuite.

The room is part of a licensed guest house with a total of six rooms
neighborhood_overview:
Quiet neighborhood - and we're sure our guests will love it too!

Rembrandsplein, the Jewish Historical Museum, the Amsterdam Museum, the Rijksmuseum, the Van Gogh and the Stedelijk Museum are within walking distance.
The opera and the Carre Theater are just around the corner. There are many restaurants on Utrechtsestraat. Close to snack bars.

De Pijp district starts 15 minutes walking from us.
host_about: Since the summer of 2023, I have been managing Guesthouse Keizersgracht after succeeding Hans. Our team is dedicated to ensuring a pleasant stay in the heart of the Amsterdam Canal Belt. With six individually designed rooms, we offer a unique experience. We also work as part of the global German Seafarer's Mission in the port of Amsterdam, providing support to Seafarers. It would be my pleasure to welcome you to Guesthouse Keizersgracht.

name: Family house  near city center in rural landscape
description: Located in a quiet neighbourhood, the house is about 20 min cycling from the central station of Amsterdam. It is a perfect place for families with children to visit Amsterdam and surroundings.
neighborhood_overview:
In a 5-minute bike ride you get to meadows or to the ancient villages Durgerdam, Holysloot, and Ransdorp, while Broek in Waterland, Marken and Volendam are close by car.

A beautiful start to explore Amsterdam North is the EYE movie centre, which is located near the ferry and gives you a wonderful view at the IJ river and Amsterdam. And at the banks at the North side of the IJ (ten minutes ride) you will find previously disused warehouses which host creative start-ups, festivals, restaurants and, once a month, mega flea market.

neighborhood_overview: The modest origins of the Jordaan (it was built to house Jewish and French immigrant workers) is still visible in its small, very old houses and the fact there is an old cafe on nearly every corner (often the type where locals will burst into folk music on Sunday drinking sessions). Nowadays these old brown cafes share space with brick oven pizzerias, boutique design shops and other trappings of the young professional set. Nice to know: each of the streets in the Jordaan is named after a flower.

Miriam

name: Charmant appartement aan de gracht
description:
A beautiful sunny apartment for 2 people on the edge of the old town in the Zeeheldenbuurt. Located in the neighborhood: the Jordaan, Westerpark, Royal Palace on Dam Square and cozy shopping street. For public transport: tram 3 to the main museums, Concertgebouw, Heineken brewery. Tram stop is nearby, Central Station is within walking distance. Supermarket at the end of the street. A bike rental is nearby.

We are happy to give tips for the nice and beautiful places in our city.
neighborhood_overview: The Western Islands across the canal are unique to walk through and through the cozy shopping street Haarlemmerstraat and -dijk you will be in the heart of the city center in 20 minutes. In this street are many nice shops and fine restaurants. The Westerpark is around the corner, for a beautiful walk or a cup of coffee in the sun. The ferry to go to the north side of the city, is within walking distance (Pontsteiger). The entire city is easily accessible by bike. And public transportation is also easy; the tram stops in front of the door.
host_about: I live in Amsterdam since a 12 years and I  do love this city a lot! I have friends and family around the neigbourhood and I work nearby as a nurse. I travel a lot myself and love to share my favorite spots in this beautiful city.

name: Modern City Centre Penthouse 3BR + Rooftopterrace
description:
Our beautiful industrial renovated 3-bedroom apartment of 130m2 is located in a quiet street, just a 10 minute walk from the famous Jordaan.

Besides 2 bedrooms with king and queen size beds there is also a children room available upon request. The house is completely child save.

And very good located from the center of Amsterdam (Leidsesquare) is by (rental) bike only 10 min. The closest train station is only 7 min by tram and from there it is another 7min by train to Schiphol airport.
neighborhood_overview: We love amsterdam-west. It is a very quite neighborhood and just 10 minute walk from the famous Jordaan. Plenty of shops just around the corner and a quick 5 stop 7 minute tram ride to the city centre. In West you will find a lot of cool hip restaurants so you can avoid those dodgy pizza places in the centre :)
host_about:
I live togheter with my girlfriend Suzanne in our own designed appartment. It took a year before everything was renovated, but now we have our dreamhouse! 
We love to travel so we are away a lot from home and want to let others enjoy our home. 

We like to watch good movies & series so we have a big 3D 55inch flatscreen  with netflix on it and a very comfi couch with loveseat to enjoy this screentime and makes it almost better as watching it in the cinema!

I have a big passion for cooking and as you see we have a open kitchen where there is everything you need, one big oven and a small oven, 6 pitt gaspit and a cookisland to prepare your 3 course menu or to bake pies & cupcakes what Suzanne likes to do. When the weather is good we can go up to the rooftopterrace and chill on the loungeset and make some burgers on the BBQ and enjoy the endless sun and nice view over Amsterdam.

We are both big music lovers and I also play the drums and have an electronic drum in the livingroom, feel free to play some tunes but keep the headset on for the neighbours.

We are very easy going people who like festivals, concerts, movie & theater a lot. Our house is in the weekends filled with friends and/or family to have nice dinners and chilltime. Our neighbourhood is very beautifull and quiet, around the corner there is the smallest canal of Amsterdam, a beautifull old mill and also a big playground for children next to the water. The street next behind ours you'll find a small shoppingstreet with big supermarket, several (take-away) restaurants, lunch & coffeeplaces, 2 drugstores, officesupplie store, flowershop and nightshops. 
We live close to hotspots where the Amsterdam-people go to such as The Marktkantine, The Foodhallen and Westerpark. We go there a lot because all three full of good food & drinks, music, party even movies and other cultural events!
We live very happy & peacefull in our house, if you rent it you will feel the good energy and the big amount of sunshine through the whole house. We do expect that if you stay here you take good care of our home while were not there. So if you want to party do it outside of the house, you're in Amsterdam enough pleaces to go to! 

We will leave a small guide, where you find everything in our neighbourhood and the public transport. We hope you will enjoy our house and Amsterdam to the fullest!

This house is situated in the heart of Amsterdam in the lively and charming Jordaan district, nearby the amazing canals, the Nine Streets and DAM square. This district is thé place to be if you are in Amsterdam.


The Jordaan is by far the most famous district in Amsterdam. It is at the west side of the amazing canals ‘grachtengordel' and it is on walking distance of the Central Station, the Dam square, the Leidseplein and public transportation. Originally it was a working-class neighbourhood, but the Jordaan is now one of the most expensive and upscale locations to live in the Netherlands. Many art galleries, particular for modern art, speciality shops, restaurants, traditional cafes, and markets characterize this romantic and historical part of Amsterdam.

name: Classic apartment, 70 m2 @De Pijp
description: Large double living space en suite divided by authentic wooden sliding doors. 1 bedroom with high sleeper for a single person. 2nd bedroom at the back of the house with a double bed. A third bed is situated in a space which is converted into a large box bed (capsule room). The restroom is separate from the shower room. Open kitchen in living space. The dining table seats 4 guests. There’s no sofa nor television. Recently work has been done to the bathroom (new shower) and the electrical circuit.
neighborhood_overview: Next to the all year round open air market Albert Cuyp in one of the liveliest quarters of Amsterdam close to the city centre. The popular neighborhood De Pijp is favored by locals, young families and students alike because of the green parks (the flat is 300m from Sarphatie-park), lively squares and the nearby Amstel river. De Pijp features probably the highest density of terraces, bars, eateries, restaurants and coffeeshops in Amsterdam. Yet the apartment itself is reasonably quiet (double glass) and peaceful. Because of the good relationship with our downstairs neighbors,  parties and loud music are not permitted. Pets are welcome.
host_about:
Animula vagula blandula 
first line of a poem by Roman Emperor Hadrian 138 AC
Meaning Little soul, little wanderer, little charmer.

Once a traveler, always a traveler. If it isn't outbound, it's inward. And it isn't about the destination. It's about the road.  Going up and down, left and right. Sometimes welcoming with lots of comfortable hide aways. Challenging at all times. 

I prefer the word Tao. Literary meaning way, path or route. Because it clarifies the point of traveling which is to cross borders, going beyond the clearly visible, the well sign posted and known world and even beyond the world of physical appearances all together. 

Many years ago I set out traveling to expand my geographical map. I end up expanding my mind map. 

I like to share with you the place I call home. As a resting place for you on your travels through life. 

I manage to earn a living as a yoga teacher with some side hustles. I run a little webshop and I work as a chef or a hostess in the catering business. I love my partner who lives oversees like he’s Romeo and I am Juliette. I love my two beautiful daughters. 

Amsterdam people are free, funny and friendly. Come on over and leave your footprint in this great travelers hub called Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview:
We live near the Albert Cuyp market in the pijp area, since July 2018 there is a new metrostop from North to South and you can take the metro to the RAI (exhibition center) and to North of Amsterdam. It is line 52
the De Pijp - the vibrant cool and trendy neighborhood with all its nightlife and food options. The historic Albert Cuyp market where you can sample some Dutch delicacies is only a block away. neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is truly in one of the most sought after areas of Amsterdam.

The Haarlemmerdijk, one block away, has been voted the best shopping street of the Netherlands many times, due to its amazing mix of vintage, design, flower and boutique fashion shops and many hip coffee places. Amsterdam's oldest cinema, The Movies, is also located there for an old school cinema experience.

The Westerpark, which hosts lots of cultural events and concerts and is only a 5 minute walk from the apartment

The ferry to the NDSM area, in the Northern part of Amsterdam, one of the city's new hotspots leaves a 10 minute walk from the apartment, through the pituresque Bickers island, with its tiny canals and old warehouses (and surprisingly a children's farm).

name: Boho chic home with luxury en suite.
description:
Cosy & very quiet home with luxury ensuite. Superb location in trendy hotspot neighborhood De Pijp, super centrally located in Amsterdam.

Many restaurants, cafés, boutique shops, and bars are just around the corner, but the apartment is in a very quiet residential street for a good night’s rest. Walking distance to some of the city's major sites, such as: Van Gogh Museum, Rijksmuseum, Vondelpark and the famous Albert Cuyp market for freshly made stroopwafels.
neighborhood_overview:
'De Pijp' is Amsterdam's most vibrant neighborhood. Close to the Museum Quarter, 'De Pijp' gives you everything you look for in Amsterdam: small, cobbled streets, nice cafes, coffee corners and one of a kind restaurants and shops. Whether you stroll down the streets or sit down on one of the many terraces, visiting 'De Pijp' shows you what Amsterdam is all about. This is the hotspot where all new things in Amsterdam are happening.

neighborhood_overview:
Westerpark is a vibrant neighborhood located in the western part of Amsterdam, the capital city of the Netherlands. It is known for its mix of residential areas, cultural attractions, and recreational spaces, making it a popular place to live and visit.

One of the prominent features of Westerpark is the park after which the neighborhood is named.

The park is also home to several cultural establishments, such as the Westergasfabriek, a former gasworks turned cultural complex that hosts art exhibitions, festivals, markets, and concerts throughout the year.

Westerpark is also known for its vibrant social scene. The area is dotted with trendy cafes, restaurants, and bars, offering a wide range of culinary experiences.

host_about:
Ik woon sinds mijn studententijd in Amsterdam, en inmiddels werk ik er als verloskundige. Het is een wereldse stad, maar toch met een dorps gevoel. IJburg is een nieuwe wijk bij Amsterdam, met prachtige architectuur. Je hebt hier de voordelen van buitenaf wonen; water, vrij uitzicht, wind, natuur, maar ook de voordelen van de grote stad heel erg dichtbij. 
Ik en mijn 3 kinderen zijn niet altijd thuis, en graag maak ik het voor anderen mogelijk om mijn huis te huren en zo Amsterdam en IJburg te leren kennen. Perfect geschikt voor gezinnen door het aantal slaapplekken en de rustige ligging, maar ook zeer geschikt voor mensen zonder kinderen, die Amsterdam en omgeving willen verkennen.
Mede door mijn werk als verloskundige heb ik de stad tot in de puntjes leren kennen en deze kennis deel ik graag met anderen.

neighborhood_overview: Bos en Lommer is my favorite area in Amsterdam to live and stay in. Up to about fifteen years ago this was not the best area of the city. Without losing its charm from back then, it has gradually changed into the highest rated residential neighborhood in Amsterdam. Here you have everything in close reach or right at your doorstep. I love the fact that I can take a direct tram to the shopping street or museum district here, or take the Amsterdam Beach line in front of my door for our rare hot days. I can walk to the popular nightclub de School, and my grocery stores are all within 200m. This area has it all for me. It lives during the days and lets you sleep during the night. Highly culturally diverse, the best Turkish restaurants are right here, as is the best typically Dutch fish shop for your daily dose of herring (raw fish, acquired taste) brought in fresh every morning from Volendam. Three parks closeby, there is always a moment to enjoy nature too.

neighborhood_overview:
De Pijp continues to breathe life as the lively bohemian district known as the Quartier Latin (Latin Quarter). The young, old, students, artists, and families have all chosen to make de Pijp their home, and far removed from the hustle and bustle of central Amsterdam, this homely alternative is appealing. It has a colourful mix of cuisines, terraces and convivial cafés. From the beautiful landscaped gardens of Sarphatipark to the famous Albert Cuypmarkt street market, De Pijp oozes beatnik flair from every angle, and is has been popular haunt for creatives, students and bohemian spirits since the 60s.

It is near the Museum quarter (10 minutes walking to Rijksmuseum and Van Gogh museum) and 5 minutes waking to Heineken experience.

name: Designed Penthouse, Amsterdam city center
description:
Modern-designed penthouse apartment with rooftop terrace in quiet neighbourhood De Baarsjes on westside of Amsterdam.
30 mins to Amsterdam Schiphol airport. 2 Mins walk to bus/tram stops. Direct transport within 15 mins to city center and all famous tourist resorts, Amsterdam Center, Amsterdam Sloterdijk etc. train stations.
neighborhood_overview:
De Baarsjes is one of the city's most multicultural 'hoods with 126 different nationalities. It's the ultimate place to go for quality cheap ethnic food. Pera (Jan Evertsenstraat is an excellent Turkish grill, while Farasa (Jan van Galenstraat has one of the best Surinamese roti in the city.

While much of the area is generic pre-war housing, it has some architectural gems. The quarter between the canal Admiralengracht and the Surinameplein is part of the 1920s idealistic urban expansion Plan West, which combined social housing with Gaudí-esque brickwork, best exemplified in the De Sieraad, Mercatorplein, and the nearby church Jeruzulumkerk (Jan Maijenstraat 14, )

A newly build 200 M2 family house, overlooking the IJsellake and with a backyard facing the south. Just a 12 minute tramride away from Central Station.

The backyard has a trampoline and a small playground next to our backyard. There is a green park connected and in summer you can swim Just behind our house!

Since we are in a family neighbourhood, we are only available for families And not for big groups of friends.

The house has big windows with stunning views.
neighborhood_overview: IJburg is a part of Amsterdam, although it feels lika a family holiday town. It is quite and neat and a nice escape from the busy city, although you are just a tramride away. IJburg has many beaches, a green parc running on one side and the big IJsellake with lots of sailing boats on the other side. IJburg has many shops, coffeebars, playgrounds and nice restaurants.
host_about:
Hoi,

name: Modern family home near major A'dam attractions
description:
* IDEAL FOR FAMILIES * 5-minute walk to cultural and festival hotspot NDSM with Student Experience NDSM * superfast in the city centre with metro 52 or free ferry * near the buzz, not in it *

- New (2014)
- Perfect to explore Amsterdam & surroundings
- Quiet residential area with families with children
- Sunny from 12-22 hrs
- 15 min. to Central Station
- Supermarket at 2-min. walk, 7 days
- 2 bathrooms, 1 with jacuzzi
- 3 toilets, 1 on each floor

neighborhood_overview:
Ideal neighbourhood for children to play in the street. Supermarket Plus around the corner, open 7 days a week.

Close to all major Amsterdam attractions: Rijksmuseum, Van Goghmuseum, Stedelijk Museum, etc.

If you head 5 minutes in the other direction, away from the centre, you are in a quiet rural area with fields and country houses. Recreation area Het Twiske, for example, where you can take a swim or just lie in the grass.

15 minutes by car to Volendam, Edam and Marken

30 minutes by car to Zandvoort beach

Highlights in Amsterdam-Noord:
- NDSM Wharf
Our house is located a 2-minute walk from creative hotspot NDSM Wharf, home to the creative industry and nice restaurants along the water.

- A'dam Toren: spectacular views, including a swing on the top roof

- EYE Film, museum & restaurant

- Nieuwendammerdijk and Buiksloterdijk: quaint historic houses, beautifully renovated
host_about:
Hi, we are family of 4 (2 sons). We are both self-employed in the communications, coaching and editing industry. We speak Dutch, German, English, French, Spanish and Sranantongo.

We are real Amsterdam aficionados. Any interest you might have, we can provide you with tips and addresses if you like. We know the city inside and out. Theatre, museums, restaurants, the yoga scene, the tango scene, architecture, you name it.

name: Charming 3-bedroom family house (120m2) & garden
description:
A beautifully located, spacious (120m2) comfortable family home with a view on a green park. It is situated close to the city centre (8 min) and near to RAI. It has 3 bedrooms, a big living room and a kitchen. Kick back and relax in the sunny garden incl. a picnic table, a 'kids castle'...and a trampoline!
The popular 'De Pijp' is just a stone's throw away from the apartment. Bus stops, metro, restaurants, green parks and grocery stores are around the corner.
neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is located in one of the most popular areas of Amsterdam called 'Rivierenbuurt'/'De Pijp'. Rivierenbuurt literally translates to ‘River neighborhood’. It's name stems from the fact that most of the streets here are named after rivers in the Netherlands. This residential neighborhood was developed in the 1920s for Amsterdam’s middle class. It was part of architect Hendrik Petrus Berlage's ‘Plan Zuid’, and was considered quite an architectural wonder in those days. Even today, architecture buffs find their way around the many examples of Amsterdam School architecture.

De Pijp is one of Amsterdam's most popular neighborhoods. Lose yourself for hours in this lively Latin Quarter of Amsterdam, with its colorful mix of cuisines, terraces and convivial cafes. From the beautiful landscaped gardens of Sarphatipark to the famous Albert Cuypmarkt street market, De Pijp oozes beatnik flair from every angle.

Our apartment is also extremely suitable for visitors
host_about:
Like most people on Airbnb we love to travel and discover new places. We like the concept of enjoying your stay local style very much. It's how we prefer to travel ourselves and experience local life abroad. Besides that we love cooking, art, theatre, cinema, skiing, biking and friends & family. 

We are the proud hosts of a nice apartment in the city centre on the edge of the most beautiful and famous park of Amsterdam: The Vondelpark. Everything this magic city has to offer is just around our corner. 

Being travellers ourselves, we do our ultimate best to give you a great Amsterdam experience. You will find all basics available (coffee, tea, juice, cookies) and all information relating to travel systems, restaurant tips etc.

If you have an early arrival or late departure, no problem. We are not a hotel and so are very flexible! And if you have any questions, feel free to ask. We love Amsterdam, know the 'off the beaten track', local places and can help you find your way in Amsterdam. We hope you enjoy the city as much as we do!

* There is a supermarket at walking distance. It is called Plus and you’ll find it at the end of the street. It’s open till 8 P.M. More supermarkets and food shops you’ll find at the mall called Banne Buiksloot or Molenwijk, which is a 20 minutes’ walk. For the best bread & fresh croissants you can go to a nice bakery called BROOD which is located near the NDSM ferry. There is also a weekly market on the Van Der Pekstraat (wed, fri & sat). Here you can buy cheap, fresh products. For the market take bus 35 till central station, bus stop Mosplein.

Things to do and see:
In Amsterdam-North:

This appartment is perfect for a small family, two couples or a group of friends.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighboorhood, Westerpark, is very beautiful, quaint, and very well connected to other parts of Amsterdam. Staatsliedenbuurt is built in the early 1900s and has a very authentic vibe. The neighborhood is architecturally pleasant with lots of trees and space and hardly any traffic.
The neighborhood itself provides within walking distance a small grocery store, a great coffee place, a couple of nice restaurants and a gym.

The Westerpark is only a 5 minute walk where you'll find some nature, great restaurants and bars, a cinema and a boat rental place. The famous Jordaan is only a 10 minute walk. Take a stroll and explore!

Obviously this neighborhood is well connected by bike to all other neighborhoods in West (less than 10 minute bike ride) and the rest of Amsterdam (Zuid 15 minute bike ride, Center 10 minute bike ride, Oost 25 minute bike ride)

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam Centrum
In addition to the world-famous historic Canal Ring, Amsterdam's City Centre district ('Centrum') is home to a host of renowned museums, charming and high-end shopping areas, fantastic culture and entertainment.

Amsterdam’s renowned art and culture and top shopping In Amsterdam’s centre you will, of course, find the magnificent Canal Ring, but there is so much more besides. The inner city, for instance, is bursting with interesting museums, sometimes hidden behind beautiful canal-side facades. The diversity of the city centre’s culture is vast, from the emotional Anne Frank House in the west of the centre, through to the upbeat nature of Science Center NEMO in the east. In between, find an inspiring collection of art and history.

Top shopping
There is a vast array of shopping opportunities, from fashion brands and chains (Nieuwendijk, Kalverstraat) through to independent innovators and inspiring market stalls, such as at Noordermarkt.

description:
Short stay!

This beautifully decorated houseboat is in a prime location near the Jordaan district, just minutes from the city center and "Noordermarkt."

The weekly markets at the "Noordermarkt" are also just around the corner on Saturday and Monday. A lovely area with many things to do and see!

Stay on he top floor of a watervilla.
2 rooms includes a bedroom and a sitting room, plus

neighborhood_overview:
This neighborhood was a unique experiment in which each original owner built their own watervilla. Every house has a base(ment) of approximately the same size (some are slightly larger / smaller). But each watervilla has a very different outdoor and indoor design & look.
Because watervillas can be more challenging than houses on the land, there's a tight community in this area – people help and advise each other, which is rare in modern cities like Amsterdam.

Nestled in the southern part of the city, Amsterdam Zuid is a neighborhood that effortlessly combines tradition with modernity. Its leafy streets are lined with charming 19th-century architecture, creating a picturesque backdrop for your exploration. But don't be fooled by its historical charm; this neighborhood is also home to some of the city's most dynamic and cosmopolitan vibes.

Take a leisurely stroll through Beatrixpark, a tranquil oasis where locals gather for picnics and relaxation. Along the way, you'll encounter the iconic Rijksmuseum, housing masterpieces by Dutch masters like Rembrandt and Vermeer, making it a must-visit for art enthusiasts.

neighborhood_overview: The modest origins of the Jordaan (it was built to house Jewish and French immigrant workers) is still visible in its small, very old houses and the fact there is an old cafe on nearly every corner (often the type where locals will burst into folk music on Sunday drinking sessions). Nice to know: each of the streets is named after a flower.

neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is a district in the city center of Amsterdam, known for its beautiful houses, nice restaurants and original shops. When in Amsterdam, it is a must to stroll through the little streets and canals. On the many bridges over the canals, you can take beautiful pictures and see why Amsterdam is called the Venice of the North. Below you find (only a short) list of six best must sees (in my opinion):
The Wester Church Tower - The landmark of the Jordaan is the Westertoren. Everywhere in the neighborhood you can see and hear the beautiful tower and its bells. It is very nice to climb the Westertoren and look over the Jordaan and the rest of Amsterdam.

Anne Frank House - Anne Frank is one of Amsterdam’s best-known historical figures. Anne and her family lived in hiding from the Nazis for more than two years in this house. name: Fabulous family home (3 bedrooms + 2 cats)
description:
Experience the joy of this spacious and warm 3-bedroom house while being close to Amsterdam's city center!

The house is situated in a green & child friendly neighbourhood in the trendy Northern part of Amsterdam.

Central station is 15 min with bike (including the free ferry) or a 5 min walk to the metro station that brings you to CS in 5 minutes.

We prefer to rent to cat-loving families that respect the tranquil neighborhood. Our two sweet cats Bowie & Grace love cuddles!
neighborhood_overview:
Green cozy and safe neighbourhood, wonderful for kids to play as its car-free. Cars are parked at the parking space (2min walk) free of charge. In summer everyone jumps into the canal (1min walk from the back garden)!

The north side of Amsterdam is one of the most creative and trendy parts of town, with new cafes and restaurants popping up all over the place. Let me know what you are looking for and I can provide you with a detailed list of new culinary hotspots, community gardens, creative hubs, artsy places etc.

Two shopping centres are at 5min walking distance and also accessible by car or public transport. City centre is 15min away with a bike or move north and within 10min you are in the nature reserve 'Het Twiske' and pass the Dutch countryside and marshy wetlands, windmills and pastoral scenes of cows, sheep, and wildflowers.

name: 150m2 central family apartment with roof terrace
description:
Located in the lively and central district of the Pijp, our 150 sqm 3 bedrooms appartement covers the 3rd and 4th floors of a building from the 30’.
It offers a fully equipped private roof terrace from where you’ll be able to enjoy a 360 view on the city.
The appartement and its location are ideal for families who want to explore Amsterdam without compromising on space and comfort.
neighborhood_overview:
The Pijp is a very lively area with lots of little restaurants, cafes and boutique shops.

The Pijp also hosts the largest daytime market of Europe, the Albert Cuyp Market, where you’ll find the traditional range of fruits, vegetables, meat, fish but also souvenirs.
You will also be able to do your groceries in the 7/7 supermarket located 100 meters from the appartement.

Families will enjoy the 2 parks located at less than 1 km from the appartement, the Sarphatipark and the Beatrix Park.

Less than 1 km from our place, you can also take a boat tour or rent your own boat (no permit needed).

The museum area (Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh and Stedelijk museums) is 1.5 kms away.

There’s a metro station located 300 meters away, allowing to reach Centraal Station in 5 minutes.

Most activities are at walking distance, but if you want to experience Amsterdam the authentic way, we leave 2 bikes at your disposal (1 electric bike with

name: Beautiful spacious sustainable house boat.
neighborhood_overview: Welcome to my house boat, located in the rapidly upcoming popular Amsterdam Noord area, just north of central station. A 15 minute walk (or 5 minute bike ride) from the Amsterdam tower, Central Station and the NDSM area. Surrounded by popular gems like "de Ceuvel", restaurant "de klaproos", Cinema "FC Hyena", "Monk"climbing hall, the "Van der Pek" street market, there is a lot of interesting stuff going on in the area. And yet, this floating sustainably built village is an oasis of tranquility in Amsterdam. Developed and built by its inhabitants these 30 houseboats form Europe's most sustainable floating neighborhood are home to 46 families in a tight knit community. Go for a swim outside, take the kayak for a ride, take a stroll in nearby Noorderpark, or take the bike up to the country side not far away.
host_about: I'm a filmmaker from amsterdam. I like arts, restaurants, travelling, concerts. I am also the founding father of this sustainable floating community called ‘Schoonschip’ in Amsterdam.

name: Stylish ground floor apartment in trendy De Pijp
description:
Enjoy a stylish experience with a vintage touch at this one-bedroom apartment located in the heart of the vibrant & trendy De Pijp neighbourhood, where the locals (not tourists) hang & reside.

Walking distance from the famous Sarphatipark, Museumplein & Albert Cuyp market.

Easily accessible ground floor property, recently furnished with new interior & lighting. Spacious living room, king-sized bed, & tranquil courtyard.

Distance from Airport: 16 mins taxi/car.
neighborhood_overview:
De Pijp is a charming, bohemian neighbourhood in Amsterdam, outside the central canal rings, and neighbouring the famous Museumplein (museum square).

It’s where the locals hang & reside, away from the busy tourist centre. It holds a lively yet welcoming character given the multitude of markets, shops and restaurants.

Famous for the Albert Cuyp market, De Pijp is also a popular destination for weekend brunches, boutique & vintage shopping, and evenings out with friends.

Streets in this neighbourhood are very green, with plants growing from every sidewalk “garden” or pots covering entire street corners.

If you want to truly experience Amsterdam from a local’s perspective, this is the place for you.

description:

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam new West is a great location close to the city centre. It's vibrant and there are plenty of parks around the corner. The apartment is close to the Sloterplas, which is a huge lake that attracts many joggers, sport enthusiast, and other people that just want to enjoy the great parks around it.

The tram stops in front of the apartment and takes you in 5-10 minutes into the city centre. Or take a bike, which will take you as well around 10 minutes to get into the city centre. The metro is only 5 minutes away and connects you easily with the metro lines of Amsterdam but also to the Dutch train railway stations.

Fancy a visit to the city of Haarlem? This will take you ~15 minutes by car or train (or 30 mins. by bike ride).

description: Welcome to our newly renovated, high-end ground floor apartment, just 50 meters from the famous Vondelpark! description: Welcome to our fantastic apartment (90m2) with garden (!) in trendy Amsterdam-Noord! 4 min. from metro station Noorderpark, and only 1 stop to Central Station. neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam Noord, in our humble opinion, is one of the best areas to feel like a true local! It offers the best of being in a quiet area, but having great restaurants, cafés and activities within minutes.
At de Van der Pek street, just a short walk away from the apartment, you can find great shopping such as Frommagerie Kef and Pek & Kleren, and the local market three times a week. Or go watch a film at FC Hyena and drink a cocktail after. Grab brunch at Café Keppler or head for superb coffee at Zithoek. Dine and feast at nearby hotspots such as Euro Pizza, Café Modern, or Skatecafe Karin & Yvonne. Grab a locally brewed beer at Oedipus Brewery. Go dance at one of the festivals in de Kromhouthal or the darkened rooms of the Shelter. Recover the next day sunbathing in Noorderpark, which we live right next to. And besides, within 5-10 min. you are in the city centre to explore even more!

My super cozy apartment is located right next to Rembrandt Park, in De baarsjes, a trendy & up-and-coming neighborhood, still central in Amsterdam but away from the annoying tourists places. This is the real Amsterdam.

The apartment is located just a few seconds walk from the beautiful Rembrandt Park.
It is still short distance from most of the city.

A bike rental is located right across the street.
neighborhood_overview:
Rembrandt Park is one of the main parks in Amsterdam (together with Vondel Park and Westerpark). Of the 3, it is the least touristy park, which makes it very pleasant for a stroll without the horde of people like in other places.

Rembrandt Park is in the area called: De Baarsjes.
De Baarsjes is one of the most up-and-coming neighborhoods in Amsterdam.
Here you can now find a wide variety of trendy coffees and shops. The trendy food halls where you can eat or shop are within walking distance.

Besides the many shops and bars you can also enjoy recreation in the area such as the Rembrandtpark or the Erasmuspark. In the summer you can sit at the waterfront with a drink or go to the nearby Vondelpark.
Most of the people living in De Baarsjes are in their 20s and 30s.

neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan neighbourhood is tucked inside central Amsterdam and quite conveniently located. Arguably Amsterdam's most famous district, the area contains an upscale assortment of art galleries, patio restaurants, cafes and street musicians.
Trendy Jordaan's narrow canals and streets are flanked by indie boutiques, cosy pubs, and hip eateries. Stalls at the Noordermarkt square market offer jewellery, clothes, antiques and organic food. Antiques Centre Amsterdam sells vintage ceramics and paintings, while smaller galleries in the area focus on innovative contemporary art. Other attractions include the Houseboat Museum and the Anne Frank Huse!

name: Luxury Familyhouse 10 minutes from Central Station
description:
The luxury house has all the comforts. You can access the newly built new garden with lovely seating chairs from the living room. On the second floor are 3 bedrooms and a bathroom. On the top floor is the master bedroom with a king size size bed.
From the house you can reach Amsterdam Centraal in 10 minutes and you will be in the heart of Amsterdam within no time. In the neighborhood you have fun activities, such as a cinema or golf course. You have nice shops and eateries at walking distance.
neighborhood_overview:
The house is located in one of the newest neighborhoods of Amsterdam-Noord. This popular neighborhood is very child-friendly with several (nature)playgrounds and sports spots. With the North-South line just a few minutes' walk away, you are in the heart of Amsterdam within 5 minutes and on the Zuidas within 15 minutes. In about 3 minutes you are by car on the A8 or A10. And within 15 minutes by bike, you will find the ferry to Centraal Station.

Shopping center Boven 't Y is within walking distance, with well-known shopping chains such as H&M, Decathlon, Hema & Albert Heijn, but also the necessary craft shops. The Pathé cinema (12 rooms), and various restaurants including “De Beren” and the recently opened “Boules & Bites Bar” are also within walking distance. Throughout Amsterdam-Noord you can find hip restaurants & bars, such as: Pompet, Il Pecorino, Cannibale Royale, the Goudfazant, Oedipus Brewery, Pllek, IJver and Loetje aan ’t IJ. Too many to mention!

name: Sunny Apartment with a balcony close to Jordaan
description:
Located between Westerpark and Jordaan, our apartment is ideal to explore Amsterdam.
In our neighbourhood you will find many shops, bars and restaurants.
The apartment itself is on the last floor (4th floor) of a typic Amsterdam building.
From the confort of our couch you can enjoy the view on Amsterdam rooftops.
On the other side of the living room you can access our blacony which is big enough to have dinner there, you will enjoy the afternoon sun from 15.00 until the night.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located between Westerpark and Jordaan

Westerpark is not just a park, but a lively neighborhood that beautifully blends nature, culture, and entertainment. The park itself is a wonderful place to relax, picnic, or even catch an outdoor movie in the summer.

The neighborhood is home to a variety of restaurants, cafes, and trendy boutiques. It's also known for the Westergasfabriek, a former gasworks factory that's now a cultural venue hosting a range of events from music festivals to food markets.

Jordaan is a picturesque and lively district known for its beautiful canals, narrow streets, and quaint houses. Once a working-class area, Jordaan has transformed into one of Amsterdam's most desirable and trendy neighborhoods.

The area is brimming with cozy cafes, unique boutiques, and art studios.
It's also home to the famous Anne Frank House and a host of other historic sites. The weekly Noordermarkt flea market is a must-visi

neighborhood_overview:
The Pijp, located near the center of Amsterdam, is known for its lively atmosphere, diverse cultural mix, and bustling streets. This neighborhood, originally built in the late 19th century, has a rich history and has evolved into one of the city's trendiest and most cosmopolitan districts.

Characteristic of De Pijp are its narrow streets, historic buildings, and vibrant markets, such as the famous Albert Cuyp Market, where you can find a variety of fresh produce, clothing, flowers, and exotic delicacies. The atmosphere is further enhanced by the many cozy cafes, trendy restaurants, and chic boutiques scattered along the streets.

The neighborhood is also known for its diverse population, with a mix of local residents, expatriates, and students contributing to the cosmopolitan atmosphere. This is reflected in the diverse culinary scene, ranging from traditional Dutch eateries to international cuisines from all corners of the world.

neighborhood_overview: Welcome to the 'Transvaalbuurt'! An upcoming neighborhood with a wide range of shops, restaurants and sports facilities. About 50 meters from the accomodation you will find a supermarket for your daily shopping, with the 'Pretoriusstraat' in its direct extension, where Slagerij Poldervaart (Butchery) is located, as well as a snackbar and various greengrocers. Ofcourse, you can also visit Oostpoort Shopping Center (8 minutes walking distance) for an even more extensive shopping experience. Around the corner, less than five minutes walk, you will find the 'Beukenplein' with various trendy restaurants such as 'bar Bru', 'Bar Bukowski' or 'La Cerveceria'. You don't have to go far for a culinary experience either, for example Restaurants 'De Kas', 'Cafe Cliche' (Sidney Schutte), 'The Cottage' and 'Lille' are all within walking distance. More into running? the Amstel area, Oosterpark and Park Frankendael are all located just around the corner.

neighborhood_overview: De Pijp is brimming with fantastic (typical Dutch) cafés, restaurants, coffee shops and bars. Of course, a visit to Amsterdam wouldn’t be the same without a trip to the famous Albert Cuypmarket, flanked by over 100 shops. If you wander down Albert Cuypstraat and Ferdinand Bolstraat, the main streets in de Pijp, you'll find many exotic and authentic Syrian, Moroccan, Surinamese restaurants, to name but a few, and a typical Amsterdam pub is located on almost every corner. description:
Experience Amsterdam's charm in a modern and cosy apartment near the City Centre with roof terrace.

In the trendy Indische Buurt, close to top tourist spots, shops, bars and restaurants. Walk or tram ride to Artis , Rembrandtplein, Dam Square, Centraal Station. neighborhood_overview: The Indische Buurt neighborhood in Amsterdam is known for its vibrant and diverse culture. It's a melting pot of different ethnicities and nationalities. The neighborhood is known for its bustling street markets like the Dappermarkt and Javastraat, where you can find exotic spices, traditional clothing and unique souvenirs. You will find a variety of restaurants and cafes serving a mix of international cuisine. The neighborhood is also home to many small, independent shops and boutiques, making it a great place to explore and discover new things. It is also a great place for those who are interested in historical and cultural sites, as there are many beautiful old buildings and monuments.

name: Luxury Houseboat-Apartment in the historic center
description:
This fully furnished houseboat, with its own terrace, has a beautiful light through the large windows in the entire living area.

This tastefully renovated and nicely decorated light Houseboat-Apartment is located on a unique historic island which is a very popular residential area on the urban island of Prinseneiland. The island is like an old-fashioned village in the center of Amsterdam and is inhabited by a nice mix of artists, expats and traditional Amsterdammers.
neighborhood_overview:
The Western Islands: Bickerseiland, Prinseneiland and Realeneiland are three islands in the center of Amsterdam. They are located south of the IJ and the “Naval heroes neigborhood” (Zeeheldenbuurt). between Central Station and Amsterdam-Sloterdijk, west of the Westerdok and east of the Planciusbuurt on the Westerkanaal. The Western Islands form the core of the Gouden Reael district, part of the Centrum district, which also consists of the adjacent Westerdokseiland, the “Haarlemmer neighborhood” (Haarlemmerbuurt) and the Planciusbuurt.

The Western Islands are a small world in themselves, are suitable for walks and nowadays often the setting for filming. From the beginning, there have been warehouses and shipyards on the Western Isles. They formed an important part of the atmosphere on the islands, a combination of working and living.

Close to the famous Jordaan area and weekly markets such as the "Noordermarkt" are also just around the corner on Saturday and Monday

In de weekenden en op zomeravonden ben ik veel buiten, op het strand om te surfen of in de omliggende natuur om te fietsen. 

Ik kijk er naar uit om je te verwelkomen in mijn fijne appartement en deel graag mijn favoriete plekken met je!

name: A Modern, Peaceful Unit in Amsterdam
description:
If you appreciate a minimalist, hotel-like atmosphere, this newly renovated 60m² apartment offers a bright, clean, and comfortable stay. If you love the character of older homes with a "lived-in" feel, this might not be the right fit.

Ideal for a single professional or a couple, the apartment provides a calm retreat while still being well-connected to the city. Please note that the front door is shared, though the space itself offers plenty of privacy.
neighborhood_overview:
Nestled in the Eastern Docklands of Amsterdam, Cruquiuseiland is a unique blend of industrial heritage and modern waterfront living. Once a bustling harbor and industrial zone, this peninsula in the Zeeburg district has transformed into a vibrant residential area, offering a perfect mix of tranquility and urban convenience.

Why Cruquiuseiland?
🌊 Waterfront Living – Surrounded by the water of the Nieuwe Vaart and the Amsterdam-Rhine Canal, offering stunning views and a serene atmosphere.
🏡 Modern Architecture Meets History – A mix of repurposed industrial buildings and contemporary new-builds create a stylish and dynamic neighborhood.
🌿 Peaceful Yet Lively – A quieter alternative to central Amsterdam, but still close to cultural hotspots, trendy restaurants, and green spaces.
🍽 Great Dining & Culture – Home to waterfront cafes, creative hubs, and restaurants like The Harbour Club and Cruquius Local, offering a mix of fine dining and casual bites.

neighborhood_overview: Occupying a roughly triangular area bordered by the stately Vondelpark to the south, the leafy and lively Oud-West (Old West) is the result of rapid urban expansion in the last quarter of the 19th Century. Amsterdam Oud-West is a dynamic neighbourhood that's home to a flurry of top-notch restaurants, hip boutiques and beautiful concept stores – many of which are found on the bustling De Clercqstraat and the Jan Pieter Heijestraat – while the Overtoom, a busy road that runs parallel to the Vondelpark, is the best place in town for furniture shopping. An increasing number of convivial coffee shops are opening their doors on the bustling Kinkerstraat, and at its intersection with Ten Katemarkt, you’ll come across one of Amsterdam’s coolest developments – De Hallen. Having undergone an enchanting renovation, this former tram depot now houses a boutique hotel, cinema, two restaurants and a food hall that’s a sheer feast of a treat for culinary connoisseurs. name: Family home in North-Amsterdam!
description: A beautiful family house located in the fantastic neighborhood of Amsterdam-Noord. The perfect base for exploring Amsterdam. The house is situated in a quiet and peaceful neighborhood, with trendy restaurants, museums, a park and shops close by. The house features three spacious and bright bedrooms, as well as a backyard where you can enjoy breakfast in the sun. We have decorated the house with a lot of love and care, and we hope our visitors will treat it with the same level of respect.
neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam Noord is the northern district of Amsterdam, situated on the opposite bank of the IJ River from the city center. It is an up-and-coming neighborhood that has undergone significant redevelopment in recent years, transforming from an industrial area to a creative and cultural hub. The district is known for its trendy cafes, hip restaurants, and art galleries, as well as its diverse cultural offerings.

Some of the notable attractions in Amsterdam Noord include the EYE Filmmuseum, a modernist building dedicated to the art of film; the NDSM Wharf, a former shipyard turned creative hotspot featuring street art and a flea market; and the A'DAM Lookout, an observation deck offering panoramic views of the city. There are also several parks in the area, such as the Noorderpark and the Vliegenbos, which provide ample opportunities for outdoor recreation.

One of the unique characteristics of Amsterdam Noord is its accessibility. The district is connected to the city

De Pijp neighbourhood is one of Amsterdam’st most fashionable areas that is famous for its boutique stores, vintage shops as well as countless quality restaurants and cosy cafes.

The flat is a one-minute walk from Amsterdam's largest street market, the colourful Albert Cuypmarkt and a three-minute stroll from the tranquil Saphatipark.

Though de Pijp is a bustling area, the flat is located on a calm side street. If you are looking for a neighbourhood that is far away from the city’s seedy “tourist zones,” de Pijp is your place to be.

Amsterdam’s Museum Quarter ( Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum) is only a 15-minute walk away. The flat is It is also easily reachable from Schiphol Airport by taxi (20 minutes) or with public transport from Central Station.

name: Lovely apartment city center
description: Welcome to my lovely apartment in Amsterdam. It is perfectly located in the city center, yet in a relatively quiet residential area. Many city centre attractions are close by, with a large choice and variety of food and drinks hospitality just around the corner. The apartment has everything for a comfortable stay to experience the city. It has a big open plan living and kitchen area, with fantastic windows and light, with a view over one of the nicest canals in Amsterdam.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the city center, but in a relatively quiet residential area. This is a part of the city center that is not flood by tourists, and has a good mix of all kinds of people (families with children, students, elderly).
All city center attractions are close by to visit (Rijksmuseum and Van Gogh Museum are 25 minutes walk for example). The Nieuwmarket is just around the corner, with many nice bars (where many local people come as well, special tip is Café Fonteyn). On Saturday there is a nice biological market. Here is also the Zeedijk (in Chinatown), for great food (Birds, both the restaurant and the snackbar are famous for its Thai food). From the apartment you can walk to the famous Negen Straatjes in 15 minutes, for many shops and sightseeing along the old canals. The Marineterrein is ten minutes walk, a very nice place to hang out (Pension Homeland is really nice for a drink or sth to eat alongside the water) and even possible to take a swim there!

name: Appartement in de Pijp
description: My apartment is in the heart of the Pijp, one of Amsterdam’s most vibrant neighborhoods. A 15-minute walk takes you to the bustling core, full of bars and restaurants, though I prefer the quieter hidden spots. It’s also 15 minutes from the city center, though we locals rarely go, as it has become too touristy. Bordering the charming East and steps from the Amstel River, the apartment offers a peaceful retreat in the quiet Diamond Neighbourhood, with the buzz just minutes away.
neighborhood_overview: De Pijp is the most vibrant part of Amsterdam. In the narrow streets of this hip district you will find numerous restaurants with kitchens from all over the world, but also classic Amsterdam pubs and cafes with terraces outside. The Albert Cuyp Market is my favorite spot of the Pijp. Here you can still find the real “Amsterdammer”. It is a melting pot of all the nationalities that Amsterdam is rich and there are also many tourists to be found. Try a herring (or stroopwafel for the sweet chews) here. Sarphatipark is also nearby. A cute park that features English gardens with ponds and lawns. Enough to see and do so!
host_about: Hi, I’m an “import-Amsterdammer” and have completely fallen in love with this city. I’m passionate about traveling and love learning new languages and discovering different cultures. During your stay, I’m happy to share my favorite spots and tips to help you experience the best of Amsterdam. I look forward to sharing my love for this city with you!

The apartment is on the ground floor, making it extremely accessible and has a sizeable garden. The living space feels open, big and light. The kitchen is fully equipped with all necessary amenities.
neighborhood_overview:
Hoofddorpplein has a very friendly and community vibe. It's part of Amsterdam-Zuid but located so close to Oud-West and the centre. It has many amazing bars, restaurants, cafes and boutique shops for groceries, clothes, flowers and more.

We have great public transport into the centre - a tram that goes from the roundabout to Centraal Station in just 20 minutes - all the way through town. And we're very close to the highway to it's easy to get an Uber from the airport or escape the city if need be.

It's located right in between Rembrant Park and Vondel Park - two of Amsterdam's nicest green areas. It's also a short walk from the Niuewe Meer and Amsterdamse Bos - two forests with lakes and water where you can run, walk and take in nature.
host_about:
Hi, I'm Harriet - a 30-something year old living in Amsterdam. 

My parents are living in Spain, my sister and brother in London. I work as a freelancer in digital and social media strategy and content. I share a beautiful home and fur-child with my boyfriend in Amsterdam, we love to cook, travel and chill. 

I co-host and rent out our family ski chalet in the French alps, my parents home in Spain and my own home too.

neighborhood_overview:
The house in Amsterdam North is centrally located and well connected with the rest of the city. With a bus just around the corner, a metro station, and a free ferry to the central station, the entire city is at your fingertips in 10 minutes. The apartment is also within walking distance of NDSM grounds, from where a free ferry goes to the center of Amsterdam. The NDSM site is known for its tasteful and varied places to eat and drink. This former wharf is the creative heart of Amsterdam North, offering a dynamic mix of art, culture, and innovation. Our unique place offers a great base to explore this area, where imposing art installations adorn the public space and industrial background is still tangible everywhere.
Looking forward to welcoming you to our apartment and helping you discover the magic of this special neighborhood.

name: Stunning canal view place
description: Welcome to my gem in Amsterdam’s beloved Jordaan district. This is a super authentic and cozy bedroom apartment offers an enchanting location and a lot of attention to detail that captures the essence of this historic city. While you stay at my place I will make sure you have all my top insider recs for exploring this amazing neighbourhood and beyond
neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan is a historic neighborhood in Amsterdam, known for its picturesque canals, charming streets, and cultural significance. It's located in the city center, just to the west of the central train station. The neighborhood is characterized by its narrow houses with gabled facades, many of which date back to the 17th century. It has been given unesco status in 2010

Jordaan has a rich history and was originally a working-class area. Today, it's a trendy and desirable place to live, with a vibrant community and a mix of boutiques, cafes, art galleries, and restaurants. It's also famous for its weekly markets, like the Noordermarkt, and its proximity to the Anne Frank House.

The neighborhood has a relaxed, bohemian atmosphere and is a great place to explore on foot or by bike. It's a cultural hub with many art studios and music venues, making it a beloved area for artists and musicians.

name: Historic Mansion in the heart of Amsterdam 304m2
description: This beautiful townhouse in the center of Amsterdam has a rich history. The four-story urban villa was built in 1865. It is close to the canals, Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, Leidscheplein, PC Hooftstraat and the trendy Utrecht street with boutiques, cafes and restaurants. It is a great city oasis for families with children, equipped with all conveniences and comforts, 5 bedrooms, 3.5 bathrooms, a TV room, a beautiful living kitchen and a large garden.
neighborhood_overview: The townhouse is located in the center of the city. Close to the Amstel River and the canals. All major museums are within walking distance. As is the Albert Cuyp market, the largest market in Amsterdam. Opposite the house is the Frederiksplein (park) and the beginning of the Utrechtsestraat, one of the hippest streets in Amsterdam with many boutiques, cafes and culinary restaurants. Around the corner you will find Amstelplein. And also the Rembrandt Square and Leidsche Square.

neighborhood_overview:
The Nieuwmarkt neighborhood is a captivating blend of historical charm and vibrant city life. Nestled in the heart of Amsterdam, this area is famous for its iconic Nieuwmarkt square, surrounded by quaint cafes, delightful restaurants, and unique shops. The square is anchored by the striking De Waag, a 15th-century building that once served as a city gate and now hosts various cultural events and a bustling market.

The neighborhood's rich history is palpable in its narrow, winding streets and canals which lead to hidden courtyards and striking architecture, telling tales of centuries past. It's an ideal spot for those eager to immerse themselves in Amsterdam's historical ambiance while staying just a stone's throw away from modern conveniences and the city's main attractions.

Nieuwmarkt is also renowned for its lively atmosphere, with an array of bars and clubs offering entertainment into the early hours. Despite its bustling nightlife, the area retains a cozy feel

name: Cute appartement in peaceful area near city centre
description: Our house was built in the 1920’s for working class people and was designed by the famous Berlage School. The north of Amsterdam has changed immensely since then and in our neighborhood, you will now find the coolest new restaurants, bars and clubs. Alongside peaceful parks, a little forest and a bike ride away from the characteristic country dike houses. The nearest metro is a 5-minute walk away and the ferry that takes you right into the city centre is a 5-minute bike ride (15 minute walk).
neighborhood_overview:
Food:
Fromagerie Kef, the best French and Dutch cheese, van der Pekplein
Bakkerij Solinger, the very best sourdough bread, NDSM Plein 27
Chateau Karlito, good nature wines, van der pekstraat 27
There is a simple market in the shopping centre Mosveld (2 minute walk) every Wednesday, Friday and Saturday.

Restaurants
Hotel de Goudfazant, a classic and all-time favorite,
Barracuda, new trendy fish restaurant,
Café Keppler, nice for breakfast and easy lunch,
Klaproos, fun and easy pizza place,
Pompet, nice place in the park perfect for kids,
Europizza, upmarket pizza place on a strip with bar next to it

Things to do:
Bicycle to NDSM in the morning to buy fresh bread at Bakkerij Solinger.
Bicycle from the Niewendammerdijk to Durgerdam. You will be amazed by the dike houses and country side.
Have a picknick in the Noorderpark around Pompet.
And of course, go into the centre :)

•⁠ ⁠Walking distance to Martin Luther Kingpark and the scenic Amstel River—perfect for a morning jog, riverside picnic, or renting a canoe on sunny days.

neighborhood_overview: The Grachtengordel West, or Western Canal Belt, in Amsterdam is a picturesque and vibrant neighborhood that embodies the charm and history of the city. This area is characterized by its iconic canals, lined with beautifully preserved 17th-century canal houses that exude classic Dutch architecture. The streets are bustling with a diverse mix of boutique shops, art galleries, trendy cafes, and cozy restaurants, offering a blend of modern amenities and historic charm. The neighborhood is known for its lively atmosphere, with locals and tourists alike enjoying leisurely strolls along the canals, scenic boat rides, and the vibrant cultural scene. Despite its central location, Grachtengordel West maintains a serene and quaint ambiance, making it a desirable place to live and visit.

name: Modern Canal Villa Amsterdam
description: Large, modern, spacious and under architecture renovated villa of 185m2 in Amsterdam Noord.  Large living room with lots of plants, modern kitchen and large windows to enjoy the expansive view over a lush large garden and water. 4 spacious bedrooms overlooking the garden and 2 modern bathrooms. On the beautiful Landsmeerdijk, dating from 1410, part of the old sea dikes in Amsterdam. A quiet, charming neighborhood just 15 minutes by bike from Amsterdam CS and 10 minutes from NDSM.
neighborhood_overview:
Very authentic piece of Amsterdam on an ancient dike that ranges back to the 15th century. The original facade of the house is from 1900 (but nothing in the interior remains from those times).
The house is situated on a wide canal (where you can swim in summer) and at the front side of the house you have a view to the 'polder' which is a birds nature reserve (it's forbidden to enter but wild live is beautiful).
There are a lot of old traditional dike houses in the streets around the 'polder' and nature reserve, so the neighbourhood has a very authentic character.

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam Centrum is the vibrant heart of the city, known for its rich history, iconic canals, and lively atmosphere. This central district is home to many of Amsterdam's most famous landmarks, including the Royal Palace, Dam Square, and the Anne Frank House. The area's narrow streets are lined with a mix of historic buildings, trendy boutiques, cozy cafes, and world-class restaurants, offering a blend of the old and new.

The charming canals of Amsterdam Centrum, crisscrossed by picturesque bridges, create a postcard-perfect setting. The district is also known for its cultural attractions, such as the renowned Rijksmuseum and the Van Gogh Museum, which are easily accessible from here. Despite its bustling energy, the area also offers peaceful spots like the Begijnhof and the many hidden courtyards scattered throughout.

neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood surrounding the Westermarkt in Amsterdam is a captivating blend of rich history, vibrant culture, and modern sophistication. Nestled in the heart of the city's UNESCO-listed Canal Ring, this area offers a unique combination of old-world charm and contemporary urban living, making it one of Amsterdam's most desirable locales.

At the core of the neighborhood is the iconic Westermarkt square, dominated by the majestic Westerkerk, Amsterdam's tallest church tower. The toll of its bells has been a comforting presence for centuries, resonating through the cobbled streets and the elegant canals that weave through the area. The Westerkerk itself is a masterpiece of Dutch Renaissance architecture, and its tower offers breathtaking panoramic views of the city, drawing both locals and tourists alike.

neighborhood_overview:
Kinkerbuurt, located in Amsterdam Old West, is a lively and dynamic neighborhood known for its eclectic mix of shops, cafes, and cultural hotspots. Its vibrant atmosphere makes it a popular destination for both locals and visitors. With a variety of markets, trendy boutiques, and a bustling nightlife, Kinkerbuurt offers a true taste of Amsterdam's urban charm.

Just a stone's throw away is the Jordaan neighborhood, renowned for its picturesque canals, narrow streets, and historic buildings. The Jordaan is filled with cozy cafes, art galleries, and unique shops, providing a charming and serene contrast to the energetic vibe of Kinkerbuurt. Both neighborhoods together create a perfect blend of excitement and tranquility, making them ideal spots for anyone looking to experience the best of Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview:
Discover the Vibrant Neighborhood of De Pijp, Amsterdam

Located in the heart of Amsterdam's lively De Pijp district, this area offers the perfect blend of tranquility and city buzz. Known for its bohemian charm, De Pijp is one of Amsterdam’s most desirable neighborhoods, offering a vibrant mix of culture, cuisine, and character.

What Makes De Pijp Special?

neighborhood_overview:
Discover the Vibrant Neighborhood of De Pijp, Amsterdam

Located in the heart of Amsterdam's lively De Pijp district, this area offers the perfect blend of tranquility and city buzz. Known for its bohemian charm, De Pijp is one of Amsterdam’s most desirable neighborhoods, offering a vibrant mix of culture, cuisine, and character.

What Makes De Pijp Special?
• Albert Cuyp Market: This iconic market is a paradise for food lovers, with fresh produce, street food, and unique finds.
• Boutique Shopping: Explore quirky shops and independent boutiques lining the streets.
• Diverse Dining: From traditional Dutch cafes to international cuisine, De Pijp is a haven for food enthusiasts.
• Green Escape: Relax in nearby Sarphatipark, a peaceful oasis for a morning jog or a leisurely picnic.
• Art & Culture: Enjoy the vibrant art scene and cultural landmarks like the Heineken Experience and the Rijksmuseum,
all within walking distance.

neighborhood_overview:
Amsterdam Oud-West is a lively and charming neighborhood that perfectly blends local authenticity with modern urban living. Nestled just outside the city center and bordering the famous Vondelpark, this area is beloved for its tree-lined streets, beautiful 19th-century architecture, and relaxed, residential vibe.

The neighborhood is full of cozy cafés, stylish boutiques, and international eateries, especially around hotspots like De Hallen—a vibrant cultural complex with a food hall, cinema, and artisanal shops. Oud-West has a creative, youthful energy while still offering the peacefulness of a well-established community.

With its excellent public transport connections and walkable streets, it's easy to explore the rest of the city, yet many guests find themselves wanting to stay and soak in the local atmosphere. It's the ideal spot for those looking to experience everyday Amsterdam life with all the comforts of a welcoming neighborhood.

Welcome to our neighborhood!

De Baarsjes is a lively and diverse neighborhood in Amsterdam where city life meets a relaxed, local vibe. Located on Maarten Harpertszoon Trompstraat, you’ll stay on a quiet, tree-lined street with charming 1930s architecture and a friendly, down-to-earth feel – all just minutes away from the heart of the city. In short, you’ll be staying in an authentic and charming part of Amsterdam – away from the tourist rush, but close to everything that makes the city special.

What to expect in the neighborhood:

Local hotspots & cafés: Within walking distance, you’ll find popular spots like e French Café, Café Cook, Pazzi, Binnenvisser, and De Hallen. Or explore the latest coffee bars and eateries along the Ten Kate Market.

Parks & green spaces: Erasmus Park is just around the corner – perfect for a morning walk, a picnic, or a jog. Rembrandt Park and Vondelpark are also nearby.

neighborhood_overview:
Discover the Vibrant Neighborhood of De Pijp, Amsterdam

The apartment is nestled in the heart of De Pijp, one of Amsterdam’s most vibrant and sought-after neighborhoods. Known for its creative energy, historic charm, and multicultural vibe, this lively area blends authentic local character with modern urban living.

Activities:
The area offers a rich variety of things to do:
• Stroll through the iconic Albert Cuyp Market, just around the corner, for fresh produce, local snacks, and artisan goods.
• Visit nearby museums, including the Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, and Heineken Experience — all within walking distance.
• Enjoy a picnic or a run in Sarphatipark, a leafy green oasis just a few blocks away.
• Explore charming streets full of concept stores, local galleries, and hidden gems.

Accessibility:
Gerard Doustraat is extremely well-connected.
